						<summary>

						<p>Two broken stones built into the steps of the tank at the Bhaṇḍārikēri-maṭha.</p>						

						<p>[Virūpā]ksha-mahārāya</p>						

						<p>This record, the middle portion of which is lost registers a gift of land, house and some money also probably to god Sōmanāthadēva of Mūṟu[kēri] by a <hi rend="italic">seṭṭi</hi> whose name is lost. <hi rend="bold">Viṭharasa-voḍeya</hi> is stated to have been governing <hi rend="bold">Bā[rakūru-rājya ?]</hi> under the command of a <hi rend="italic">daṇṇāyaka</hi> who was a <hi rend="italic">mahāpradhāna.</hi></p>						

						<p>The extant portion of the date refers to the bright fortnight of the month of <hi rend="bold">Vaiśākha.</hi> The king, only the letter of whose name <hi rend="italic">(ksha)</hi> is preserved, must be Virupāksha.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
